<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="111" type="description">
<paragraph pageId="6" pageNumber="111">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="6" pageNumber="111">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="111">Shrub or small tree</emphasis>
2.5- 4.5 m tall; 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="111">leaves</emphasis>
chartaceous, blades 5-10 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
4.1-6.2 cm, widely elliptic, glabrescent adaxially, wooly abaxially; 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="111">heads</emphasis>
short pedunculate in clusters of 3-5 at the apex of branches, surrounded by leaves, few clusters per plant; 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="111">involucre</emphasis>
campanulate (especially at early flowering), 13-15 mm tall 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
10-12 mm wide, bracts in 5-7 series, woolly adaxially; 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="111">flowers</emphasis>
ca. 50 per head; 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="111">corollas</emphasis>
yellow, 12 mm long; 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="111">anther</emphasis>
base caudate, tails ca. 1 mm long, entire; 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="111">pappus</emphasis>
ca. 9 mm long, bristles uniseriate, broadening, flattened, and somewhat darker at the apex.
</paragraph>
